- Context: This is the second page of a document regarding Energy Isolation (EIP) & Lockout/Tagout (LOTO) planning. It continues with Core Principles and lists Isolation Planning Principles.
- Text: Safety as Standard (continued)

All isolations will be verified before work commences.

• Isolate – remove all sources of energy.
• Lock – apply locks to secure the isolation points.
• Tag – apply tags to clearly identify the isolation point and purpose.
• Test – verify that the isolation is effective and that the equipment is safe to work on.

5. Isolation Planning Principles

1. Identify all sources of energy that need to be isolated.
2. Determine the appropriate isolation methods for each energy source.
3. Develop a detailed isolation plan that includes the following:
  • The scope of the isolation
  • The equipment to be isolated
  • The isolation points
  • The isolation methods
  • The locks and tags to be used
  • The verification methods
  • The persons responsible for the isolation
  • The duration of the isolation
4. Communicate the isolation plan to all affected personnel.
5. Implement the isolation plan in a safe and controlled manner.
6. Verify that the isolation is effective before work commences.
7. Maintain the isolation for the duration of the work.
8. Remove the isolation in a safe and controlled manner after work is complete.

