5. What is Energy Isolation?
Energy Isolation is the process of controlling all energy sources to ensure equipment is in a
safe, de-energised state prior to work.
6. Identification of Energy Sources (Checklist)
Before isolation, identify all potential energy sources:
Electrical
•
Mains power
•
Stored electrical energy (capacitors, batteries)
Mechanical
Moving parts
Stored kinetic energy (springs, flywheels)
Hydraulic
•
Pressurised fluids
0
Accumulators
