7. Isolation Hierarchy
Apply the hierarchy of isolation:
Physical Isolation (Preferred)
•
Disconnection
0
Blanking/spading
0
Removal of components
Double block and bleed
Procedural Isolation (Where physical not possible)
Locking off switches
•
Control system isolation
•
Administrative controls
Always prioritise physical isolation where reasonably practicable.
