9. Verification – Prove Dead / Zero Energy
Verification is critical before work begins:
• Test for absence of voltage (approved tester)
0 Confirm mechanical parts cannot move
• Release stored energy (bleed, vent, discharge)
• Try-start or functional test where appropriate
No work starts until zero energy is confirmed.

10. Dynamic Risk Considerations
Reassess if:
0
•
0
Isolation integrity is compromised
New energy sources are identified
Work scope changes
Environmental conditions change

11. Reinstatement Controls
Before re-energisation:
• Work area cleared
• All personnel accounted for
• Guards and safety devices reinstated
0
•
Tools and equipment removed
Locks removed by person who applied them
Controlled restart procedure followed

12. Interface with Permit to Work (PTW)
Energy isolation must align with PTW systems:
• Isolation referenced within permit
• Permit issuer verifies isolation
0
Permit closure linked to safe reinstatement
Clear communication between permit roles

